  <body style="margin:0;background:#0a0a0f;color:#e4e4e7;font-family:'Inter',system-ui,-apple-system,sans-serif;-webkit-font-smoothing:antialiased;">
    <section class="hero" style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;align-items:center;justify-content:center;text-align:center;padding:6rem 1.5rem 4rem;min-height:80vh;background:linear-gradient(180deg,#0a0a0f 0%,#0e0e1a 50%,#0a0a0f 100%);position:relative;overflow:hidden;">
      <div style="position:absolute;top:-50%;left:-50%;width:200%;height:200%;background:radial-gradient(circle at 30% 50%,rgba(59,130,246,0.08) 0%,transparent 60%),radial-gradient(circle at 70% 50%,rgba(59,130,246,0.05) 0%,transparent 60%);pointer-events:none;"></div>
      <div class="hero-content" style="position:relative;max-width:800px;width:100%;">
        <div style="display:inline-flex;align-items:center;gap:0.5rem;padding:0.375rem 1rem;border-radius:9999px;font-size:0.8rem;font-weight:500;color:#93c5fd;background:rgba(59,130,246,0.1);border:1px solid rgba(59,130,246,0.2);margin-bottom:2rem;letter-spacing:0.05em;text-transform:uppercase;">
          Open source · Apache 2.0
        </div>
        <h1 style="font-size:clamp(2.5rem,6vw,4rem);font-weight:800;line-height:1.1;color:#fafafa;margin:0 0 0.5rem;letter-spacing:-0.03em;">
          Alert correlation that<br />
          <span style="background:linear-gradient(135deg,#3b82f6,#60a5fa);-webkit-background-clip:text;-webkit-text-fill-color:transparent;background-clip:text;">actually helps at 3am</span>
        </h1>
        <p class="tagline" style="font-size:clamp(1.1rem,2vw,1.35rem);color:#a1a1aa;line-height:1.6;margin:0 0 1.5rem;max-width:600px;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;">
          Junando correlates alerts from your observability stack and delivers actionable incident context directly to Slack or Teams.
        </p>
        <p class="value-prop" style="font-size:1rem;color:#a3a3a3;line-height:1.7;margin:0 auto 1rem;max-width:560px;">
          Instead of raw alerts flooding your channel at 3am, your team gets one structured message per incident with probable cause and recommended steps.
        </p>
        <p style="font-size:0.85rem;color:#737373;line-height:1.6;margin:0 auto 2.5rem;max-width:560px;">
          Built for engineering teams running multi-service observability stacks.
        </p>
        <div class="hero-cta" style="display:flex;gap:1rem;justify-content:center;flex-wrap:wrap;">
          <a href="/getting-started/" class="cta-primary" style="display:inline-flex;align-items:center;gap:0.375rem;padding:0.75rem 1.75rem;border-radius:0.5rem;font-size:1rem;font-weight:600;color:#fff;background:linear-gradient(135deg,#3b82f6,#2563eb);text-decoration:none;transition:all 0.2s ease;box-shadow:0 4px 14px rgba(59,130,246,0.3);">
            Get Started →
